interaction.content: Celebrate #internationalwomensday by booking tickets to @vamuseum and the future #makingherselfup exhibition. Not only did Frida Kahlo paint her personal struggle in a male dominated art world at the time, she also had her own body as a battlefield as a lifelong companion. Seeing her costumes and corsets in 2015 at her house made me realise just how she used these as an armour and a weapon. Her personal belongings and clothing are shown for the first time outside Mexico after having been locked away for 50 years. I can’t wait!

interaction.content:
smile.
I tend not to smile a lot. I got bullied a lot about my gap teeth, I pretty much hated more features about me as a result as time went by and the insecurities manifested into something bigger then myself. darkness just consumed every part of me cause I allowed someone that isn’t even in my life anymore define my own structure of what God made, are you mad? I’m giving someone power over me. are you normal? are you? are you normal?
I don’t care what people think, in actual fact I don’t let nobody else have power over me. your words can’t destroy a part of me that was built up through love. smiling and making jokes to people was just an ice breaker to laugh away the pain, it’s not pain anymore. it’s joy. it’s happiness in its purest form. it’s my tool, not my weapon. 
I smile now and embrace what God gave me. I made peace with my past, and I move forward. I smile now and I bring joy to peoples lives cause without people, we won’t be here. so smile and show the world what you’re made of. what’s there to fear but fear itself? move through, move on, and move beyond. 
you got this. and oh yeah, smile :relaxed:
